ezstream
------------------------------------------
Ezstream is a command line source client for Icecast media streaming servers.
It began as the successor of the old shout utility, and has since gained a
lot of useful features.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.3.33-1
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libiconv2-1.14-3
  libshout3-2.3.1-1
  libssp0-4.9.2-3
  libtag_c0-1.9.1-1
  libxml2-2.9.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.icecast.org/ezstream/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.xiph.org/releases/ezstream/ezstream-0.6.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack ezstream-0.6.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./ezstream-0.6.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ezstream-0.6.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/ezstream-0.6.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(ezstream)
